{"editorCode":";         Circling the Square\r\n\r\n;Alicia wants to make a procedure that would construct a square inscribed in a circle of radius :r. She made the procedure \"square_in_circle\", but something went wrong. Can you help her fix the procedure? \r\n\r\n;------------------------------\r\n\r\nto circle :a \r\nrepeat 360 [fd :a rt 1]\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\ncircle 1\r\n;--------------\r\nto square :r \r\nrt 45\r\nrepeat 4 [fd :r*sqrt(2) rt 90]\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\nsquare 45\r\n;-----------\r\nTo  square_in_circle :a :r\r\ncircle :a\r\nsquare :r\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\nsquare_in_circle 1 45\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"\t\t\tCircling the Square\n\n************************************\n\nTASK 1 \n...............................\n1. Run the procedure \"circle\". Compose a conjecture about the role of the variable :a. Test your conjecture by trying different values for the variable :a using the variation tool. \n\n   •    In what way does the avatar construct the circle?\n   •    Is this the same way as when it is constructed on the paper?\n   •    If not, what is the difference between the way of construction by the avatar and the one on the paper?\n\n2. Run the procedure \"square\".\n\n   •    Can you compute its diagonal? \n\n  Compose a conjecture and test it using the variation tool.\nComplete the diagonal of the square at the procedure \"square\".\n\n\nTASK 2\n.................................\n1. Run the procedure \"square_in_circle\".\n\n   •    What were you expected to be constructed by the avatar?\n   •    Where is the problem?  \n\n  Change the step value of the variable :a to 0.1 and try many different values for each variable using the sliders of the variation tool. \n\n2. For which value of the variable :r is the square inscribed in the circle?\n\n   •   Can you form a general conclusion on the value of the radius :r of the circle for which the arc of the circle that corresponds to a side of the square has the same length as the radius :r of the circle?\n\nTASK 3\n.................................\n   Complete the procedure square_in_circle properly in order to always inscribe a square in a circle for any possible value of the variable :a (using only the variable :a).\n\n\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\t------------------\n\t\t\t         \tTIPS\n\t\t\t\t-------------------\n\nTASK 2\n.................................\n1.The square isn't inscribed in the circle as the arc that corresponds to each side of the square isn't of the same length as the radius :r of the circle. \n2. :r = 57,3 approximately, when :a = 1. \n  An arc has the same length as the radius of the circle when the central angle of the circle, that is formed by this arc, is approximately 57,3 degrees.\n\nTASK 3\n.........................\n  :r = 57,3*:a\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}